    <stitle>5 SPEED AND 6 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON SERIES - DISASSEMBLE - MAINSHAFT ASSEMBLY (FS-5205)</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="disassemble" graphiccount="2">
        <title>MAINSHAFT ASSEMBLY (FS-5205)</title>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>During disassembly, lay all parts on a clean bench in the order of removal to facilitate
                    assembly.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>Use caution when removing 1st gear as the needle bearings are loose under 1st gear.</para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <para>The following steps correspond to the numbers in
            <hotlnk xrefid="f1302671">Figure 71</hotlnk>.
        </para>
        <figure id="f1302671" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1302671" filename="../figg13/G1302671.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 71. Disassemble Mainshaft Assembly (FS-5205)</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">With the mainshaft front facing up, install the mainshaft assembly vertically in a vise.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove 4th-5th speed synchronizer and cups.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the shift hub thrust bearing and bearing race.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove 4th-5th clutch hub.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove 4th gear and 4th gear bearing.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove 3rd gear retaining snap ring.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove 3rd gear thrust washer and locating ball.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove 3rd gear and 3rd gear bearing.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove 2nd-3rd speed synchronizer and cups.</para>
        </step1>
        <para>The following steps correspond to the numbers in
            <hotlnk xrefid="f1302672">Figure 72</hotlnk>.
        </para>
        <figure id="f1302672" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1302672" filename="../figg13/G1302672.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 72. Disassemble Mainshaft Assembly (FS-5205)</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">With the mainshaft rear facing up, install the mainshaft assembly vertically in a vise.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use a puller to remove the mainshaft rear bearing.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove 1st gear split washer retaining ring.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Separate split washers and remove half rings.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove 1st gear and 1st gear bearing.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove 1st-reverse sliding clutch.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove 1st-reverse clutch hub snap ring.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove shift hub.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove reverse gear and reverse gear bearing.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove 2nd gear split washer retaining ring.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove 2nd gear split washer and locating ball.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove 2nd gear and 2nd gear bearing.</para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
